The paper deals with compressive sensing (CS) and sparse signal recovery from binary measurements. The paper also mentions the use of adaptive sampling strategies to reduce the number of measurements required for exact recovery. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the fundamental limits of data compression, communication, and information processing. The paper also deals with signal processing and machine learning techniques, which are covered in cs.SP (Signal Processing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of high-dimensional geometry and numerical analysis, which are covered in cs.MM (Mathematical Methods) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
